OL,3,C'A death warrant': Mum's warning over
OL,4,Cson's care needs
OL,6,FThe Western Trust has warned if Lee
OL,7,Fneeds more advanced breathing
OL,8,Fequipment - known as a BiPap machine -
OL,9,Fhe won't be able to be looked after at
OL,10,Fhome as carers aren't allowed to be
OL,11,Ftrained to use the machine.
OL,13,FThe machine supplies pressurised air
OL,14,Finto his airways.
OL,16,FHis mum Caroline Wheeler said she
OL,17,Fcould not understand why carers are
OL,18,Fnot being trained to deliver the care,
OL,19,Fespecially given they have been using
OL,20,Fsimilar equipment - a CPap - with Lee
OL,21,Ffor years.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/11
