OL,3,C'A death warrant': Mum's warning over
OL,4,Cson's care needs
OL,6,FThe teenager was born with a clot on
OL,7,Fhis brain and was left with profound
OL,8,Fdisabilities including serve epilepsy
OL,9,Fthat could kill him.
OL,11,FHis mum Claire Lindsay who gave up her
OL,12,Fcareer to care for her son wanted to
OL,13,Fuse her direct payments for a carer
OL,14,Ftwo nights a week so she could have
OL,15,Fsome respite.
OL,17,FThe Trust, however, refused because it
OL,18,Fcan't provide epilepsy training and
OL,19,Fthe carer can't administer Mathew's
OL,20,Fmedication through his feeding tube.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/11
